  "body": "running `forge init --force` in an existing directory fails now if `lib/ds-test` already exists (as it should if you run `forge init && forge init --force`).\r\n\r\nProblematic line: https://github.com/gakonst/foundry/blob/0f9fa92e623f079b32e4c4256ac4844020297bf3/cli/src/cmd/init.rs#L124-L125\r\n\r\nWe should add a check: if we're in a git repo, check if `lib/ds-test` exists, if it doesn't, we install, otherwise we call it with no dependencies (to make sure deps are at least pulled properly)\r\n\r\n_Originally posted by @onbjerg in https://github.com/gakonst/foundry/issues/779#issuecomment-1049138241_",
